load ../flow-autofail.maude

--- Coverage: a self-terminating flow with an unhandled failed effect reaches the
--- failed terminal -- the workflow auto-fails instead of stalling.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-FLOW-AUTOFAIL :
  flowSelfTerminating effFailedUnhandled(e1) running
  =>* instanceFailed RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: a handled failure settles via its own terminal (the handler path is
--- reachable, so the model is not vacuously inert).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-FLOW-AUTOFAIL :
  flowSelfTerminating effFailedHandled(e1) running
  =>* settled(e1) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: with one handled and one unhandled failure in the same
--- self-terminating flow, the unhandled one still drives the auto-fail -- a
--- settling sibling does not mask the unhandled failure.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-FLOW-AUTOFAIL :
  flowSelfTerminating effFailedHandled(e1) effFailedUnhandled(e2) running
  =>* instanceFailed RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite (scope): without flowSelfTerminating, an unhandled failure never
--- auto-fails. The RESIDUAL soup var means an auto-fail in ANY reachable state
--- would be a solution, so No solution proves the non-self-terminating flow is
--- left to the broader workflow-liveness lint -- the same scoping flow-liveness
--- uses. If [autofail] dropped the flowSelfTerminating requirement this would
--- find a solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-FLOW-AUTOFAIL :
  effFailedUnhandled(e1) running
  =>* instanceFailed RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite (handled-ness): a handled failure in a self-terminating flow never
--- auto-fails. If [autofail] keyed on any failed effect rather than only the
--- unhandled disposition this would find a solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-FLOW-AUTOFAIL :
  flowSelfTerminating effFailedHandled(e1) running
  =>* instanceFailed RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite (all-handled): when every failure in a self-terminating flow is handled,
--- nothing auto-fails even though the flow is a terminal path.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-FLOW-AUTOFAIL :
  flowSelfTerminating effFailedHandled(e1) effFailedHandled(e2) running
  =>* instanceFailed RESIDUAL:Cfg .
